---
const reasons = [
  {
    number: "01",
    title: "Word of mouth still ends in a Google search.",
    description:
      "Even the best referral gets looked up. When someone hears your name, the first thing they do is search, and if nothing comes up, or just an old Facebook page, that warm lead cools off fast. A website turns referrals into booked work.",
    image: "/01-quick-check.png",
  },
  {
    number: "02",
    title: "A Facebook page isn't enough.",
    description:
      "Facebook is great for staying in touch, but you don't own it, the algorithm decides who sees you, and plenty of customers aren't on it. Your website is the one place you control, with services, hours, and contact info always in one spot.",
    image: "/02-home-base.png",
  },
  {
    number: "03",
    title: "A real website makes you look ready.",
    description:
      "You don't need a big marketing budget to look established. A clean, fast site signals you're a real, trustworthy business. That's often the deciding factor when someone's choosing between you and a competitor with no presence.",
    image: "/03-trust-signal.png",
  },
];
---

<section class="py-20 md:py-28 bg-warm-100 overflow-hidden">

  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-10 lg:gap-16 items-center mb-14 md:mb-16">
      <div data-reveal>
        <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-dark">
          A website creates instant credibility for your business, letting customers know you're serious.
        </h2>

        <div class="relative mt-8 rounded-2xl bg-white border border-warm-300 p-6 md:p-8 overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <div class="absolute left-0 top-0 bottom-0 w-1.5 bg-primary"></div>
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-primary mb-3">
            The moment you're not there for
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-warm-700 leading-relaxed">
            Someone hears your name from a neighbor, a job site, or a flyer, and does what
            everyone does now: they pull out their phone and look you up. In about ten seconds
            they decide whether you're real, reachable, and worth calling. If nothing comes up,
            or just an old Facebook page, they move on to the business that showed up ready.
            That happens dozens of times a month, and you never see the customers you lose.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end order-first lg:order-last" data-reveal>
        <img
          src="/made-in-greene-logo-big.png"
          alt="Made in Greene, proudly serving Greene County, Tennessee"
          class="w-full max-w-xs sm:max-w-sm lg:max-w-lg"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 border-y border-warm-300">
      {reasons.map((reason, i) => (
        <div
          class:list={[
            "relative py-9 md:py-10 md:px-8",
            i > 0 && "border-t md:border-t-0 md:border-l border-warm-300",
          ]}
          data-reveal
          style={`--reveal-delay: ${i * 100}ms`}
        >
          <img
            src={reason.image}
            alt=""
            class="w-full aspect-[4/3] object-cover rounded-2xl mb-6"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <div class="mb-8">
            <span class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-extrabold text-primary leading-none">
              {reason.number}
            </span>
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-dark mb-4 leading-tight">
            {reason.title}
          </h3>
          <p class="text-warm-600 leading-relaxed text-base">
            {reason.description}
          </p>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mt-14 md:mt-16" data-reveal>
      <p class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-warm-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
        A website starts at a one-time <span class="font-semibold text-dark">$950</span>. Think of it
        as a salesperson that works nights, weekends, and holidays, and never asks for a raise. For most
        local businesses, one or two jobs earns it back.
      </p>
      <a
        href="/services"
        class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-primary text-white font-semibold rounded-xl hover:bg-primary-dark transition-all hover:shadow-lg hover:shadow-primary/25 hover:-translate-y-0.5"
      >
        View Website Packages
        <svg class="w-5 h-5 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

